sec.p:
The XRD pattern of B-TiO2 NPs is shown in Fig. 1. All the diffraction peaks in the XRD patterns can be indexed to JCPDS no. 01-073-1764 which corresponds to tetragonal structure of TiO2. XRD pattern confirms the formation of pure anatase phase as no peaks corresponding to any other polymorphous are present. The XRD pattern also reveals that the B-TiO2 NPs are crystalline in nature. The average crystallite size of B-TiO2 is calculated using Debye–Scherrer’s equation and found to be ~ 50 nm:Fig. 1
